  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Hemolysis damage accumulation methodology follows the power-law model described in the primary reference (referencesIdentifier: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003), which provides the updated empirical exponents used in this analysis.",
